---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Cookie Policy"
  description="Learn about how AI Code Academy uses cookies and similar technologies."
>
  <div class="container legal-content">
    <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
    
    <section class="policy-section matrix-shadow">
      <h2>1. What Are Cookies</h2>
      <p>Cookies are small text files that are placed on your device when you visit our website. They help us provide you with a better experience and allow certain features to work.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section matrix-shadow">
      <h2>2. Types of Cookies We Use</h2>
      <div class="cookie-types">
        <div class="cookie-type">
          <h3>Essential Cookies</h3>
          <p>Required for the website to function properly. Cannot be disabled.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cookie-type">
          <h3>Functional Cookies</h3>
          <p>Enable enhanced functionality and personalization.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cookie-type">
          <h3>Analytics Cookies</h3>
          <p>Help us understand how visitors interact with our website.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section matrix-shadow">
      <h2>3. Managing Cookies</h2>
      <p>You can control and/or delete cookies as you wish. You can delete all cookies that are already on your computer and you can set most browsers to prevent them from being placed.</p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-content {
    padding: 2rem 0;
  }

  h1 {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .policy-section {
    padding: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    background-color: rgba(71, 212, 105, 0.05);
    border: 1px solid var(--brand-color);
  }

  .cookie-types {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .cookie-type {
    padding: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--shadow-color);
  }

  .cookie-type h3 {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--brand-color);
  }
</style>